| Range low reclaim setup: Altcoins | 

> What and how?
It's my favorite pattern to trade, appearing on the total altcoin market cap chart. 

You wait for the reclaim, buy the range lows, and sell the range highs and above. Invalidation: acceptance below the range low again. 
> 2019
Accumulated Bitcoin after the reclaim. I got caught by the covid crash, but I held on to my setup and stuck to the exposure. It was hard, but not capitulating on a setup and sticking to the plan worked in the end. 

> Same setup, different time frames. 

- 5-minute chart range low reclaim
It would have been easy to hold if this above were a 5-minute chart. It takes not that long—maybe an hour—to invalidate or take off. The downside is only a couple of % max. On the other hand, the upside would also only be around 10%. 
- Weekly chart range low reclaim
Now it's appearing on the weekly, the same trade setup, a range reclaim, and should be played the same. But this time, it's suddenly super hard. Because after the reclaim, we ain't doing a retest within an hour; no, it could take months and months of painful chop. Not with a couple of %, but with a potential 50% plus retraces. On the other hand, the upside is hundreds of %.
> How I'm playing this.

1. Getting in:

I've had three major moments buying Altcoins.

- Once Bitcoin reclaimed the range low, I started buying majors like SOL. I knew Altcoins would likely mirror the Bitcoin chart with a little delay. (check chart 1 in this post)

- Once the Altcoin chart reclaimed the range low.

- Both of these entries are still very profitable. My most recent buying spree is slightly underwater (smaller caps like pups), slightly up on majors (SOL), or around BE. It will depend on the short-term market direction, and I'm okay with that. I started adding the 0.25 reclaim of the range in the first quarter. Now the question is if that will hold; if not, we could have a few more months of downside chop, potentially reaching the range low again.

- Another range low (zone) retest would be another entry opportunity. 

2. Paying yourself
I recognize the downside and how hard it could be to hold on to this chart, so I figured I could A) grow my exposure in the range low and B) pay myself on wins (in dollars). For example, I've been buying SOL well below $30 on my first buying spree. Once I was up 200-300%, I took out 10-20% of the profits in dollars without the intention of putting them back in.

3. Simplify things
- I don't care about tomorrow's or next week's prices. I only care about the chart pattern to play out and playing it properly.
Betting on the direction and executing is hard work. Why would you make it even harder for yourself by including a time frame, other noise, etc.? 
I don't care how this pattern plays out; we could chop months and months and go down much more. I care about finding buy spots within the low range, having an invalidation, and having a target. 

4. MAX PAIN
The Max pain scenario for Altcoins, while not invalidating this setup, would be a fail of the first quarterly range level (the 0.25).

If reclaimed properly, the 0.25 acts as a launch path and starting point for parabolic prices, as shown on the chart below.

But if the 0.25 fails to hold after a reclaim, we're opening ourselves up again to the first quarter's lowest range of this range. After confirming the deviation, the range low again becomes a target until we invalidate this by reclaiming the 0.25 once again.

We're now fighting to hold the support, but if it fails, don't rule out another 3-6 months of chop and more downside for Altcoins.

(see how, in 2019, the 0.25 failed to hold, and we retested the lows again)
TLDR:

- Bullish on Altcoins. I believe Altcoins will mirror the Bitcoin chart, with the lag they always have, and this pattern has a very high win rate for me, especially on higher time frames like this.

> Altcoins?!

My perspective on Altcoins for the rest of this year:

> Cycle over or not?
> Where do we bottom?
> Trigger to go up?
> When?

Let's dive in:

If we can crack this trendline, I believe we'll enter the intense Altcoin bull cycle, which we call altseason. 

Read along:

| Short-term update; altcoin range |

- HTF scenario
- LTF Altseason triggers and scenario (entry thoughts)


-- 

1. HTF SCENARIO
Please read the long post I linked here: https://x.com/damskotrades/status/1804773987332792802… for an in-depth look at my crypto cycle views and higher-time frame altcoin plan.

In short, I'm playing the higher time frame range low deviation, and reclaim, just like I did with Bitcoin.

> Wait for the deviation to form and the reclaim.
> Buy the lowest part of the range; range low into its 0.25 level, which is the first quarter. Here, "buy" means getting Altcoin exposure.
> Sell Altcoins in the highest quarter of the range; 0.75 into the range high. Here, "sell" means decreasing Altcoin exposure.
> Increase selling after breaking into price discovery during a parabolic run to eventually scale out fully.

So, again, as you can see below. I'm betting on:
a) this range low reclaim to play out and 
b) Altcoins to follow Bitcoin as they always do on higher time frame moves.

I don't care about how exactly on the lower time frames. I carefully took exposure since it was below the range low (why before the reclaim; Bitcoin already reclaimed, and Altcoins usually follow) and after the reclaim. 
But for educational and potential new entry purposes we will dive one-time frame lower to identify zones of interest, dip opportunities, and potential triggers for an alt season.

2. LTF TRIGGERS AND SCENARIO

So, what do we have here in this Altcoin market cap range? We have a higher-time frame bullish range low reclaim setup and a higher-time frame bullish market structure (higher highs and lows).

However, since this is a higher time frame range, the upside is amazing, but the potential downside, without invalidating our setup, is also significant. A small move toward the range lows could mean months of chop and 30%+ more downside.

I'm not necessarily expecting it, and I won't sell the positions I accumulated (many of which much lower) because that's not how I think one should play a range deviation like this. You buy the lows, sell the highs, and don't flip-flop in between.

However, it's good to acknowledge the probability of another few months of chop and a range-low retest.

It would be very similar to what Bitcoin did in 2019.

Just like how deviations work at the range high and low and get sent to the opposite side of the range, deviations also work on the smaller parts of a big range. 

Deviate below the 0.25 level of the range, and the range low becomes more likely.
2019 Bitcoin:

> Confirm the higher time frame (HTF) range low reclaim and bullish market structure (MS), targeting the range high.
> Rejection at the mid-range.
> Deviation below the 0.25 level and into the range low before heading to our original target, the range high and above. (Please, don't comment "But COVID crash, sir.")

Currently, we have deviated below the 0.25 level. Again, I'm not selling because we're still macro-bullish, and I'm sticking to my HTF range deviation plan.

However, it's good to consider potential scenarios if you are looking for an entry.

As we're currently below the 0.25 level, it could become a bearish retest on the LTF; we could dive again into the lower part of the macro range, such as this bullish demand zone.

In my opinion, this would be a great spot to get in, rather than fully allocating yourself now while we retest it.
But again, I'm not selling to buy back lower. I've been taking profit during this cycle on wins, but with the purpose of just taking it slowly out in case I'm wrong. 

If I had zero Altcoin exposure, I would forget about the lower time frames and buy some positions here since it's on the lower part of the HTF range. It's all about slowly building positions and having a plan for it (like we're making right now, lol).

Another great opportunity and potential trigger would be a reclaim of the 0.25 (first quarter resistance) of this range. 

The 0.25 level often triggers the parabolic stage 5 run towards the range high.

If we can reclaim it and turn the lower time frame market structure bullish again, there's a high probability that this could start a parabolic run and alt season, driving prices into the highs and potentially higher.
I also marked the other 0.25 flip or reclaim events on the chart to show how they start the parabolic runs.

So TLDR:

> HTF Altcoins: bullish, sticking to a macro plan since 2023.
> HTF cycle: bullish, but always take profits on big wins into fiat without intending to reinvest immediately.
> LTF: Great Altcoin buy-the-dip opportunity, in my opinion, at the low-demand range.
> LTF: Great Altcoin trigger could be another reclaim of the 0.25 range level.

Sorry for the long text; it's for educational purposes on how I play a cycle and use a range. Make your own plan, but my DMs will be open for help.

I think the mix of...

- Starting the second part of the bull, and Altcoins starting theirs
- ETHBTC reversing
- ETH ETF inflow

... will make the Altcoin market less PvP, less centralized on certain narratives, and more inclusive for Ethereum and utility projects. It won't be like the "throw the dart" seasons of 2017 or 2021, but it will be a bit less PvP compared to now.

The 2024 meme coin mania compared to the 2017 ICO mania and the 2021 metaverse mania:

People have compared the recent meme coin mania with the altcoin manias of 2017 and 2021. 2017 we had the ICO mania, and in 2021, the Metaverse mania. 

I don't think they're the same. In 2017 and 2021, the rest of the world participated in this mania, and the Altcoin market cap went parabolic into new highs. 
Total 2 and 3 previous cycle top manias. 
Currently, we're still in the orange/purple zone of the previous range, which is not comparable to previous cycle mania tops. It's more like the DeFi summer of 2019, with only the diehards participating and lots of PVP.

We might have formed a local top, similar to 2019, and it could take longer to move up. Recently, we broke below the 0.25 level of this range and retested it as resistance.

For me, it's simple:

Higher time frame range: 
> Bullish
Medium-time frame: 
> Below the 0.25 resistance; not a great place to enter. Waiting for a break back above or a dump closer to the range lows.

-----
It would be tough to see a retrace back to the range lows, which could take months, but hang in there fam. From a macro range perspective, it's the most rewarding place to get exposure.

Here are a few examples that followed a similar macro range and cycle of price action:

- Bitcoin 2019
- FET 2023

1. Reclaim the macro range low and print the first higher high.
2. Run into the mid-range (0.5) and face rejection.
3. Deviate back below the 0.25 level.
4. Retest the range low zone.
5. Break back above the 0.25 level and start phase 5: the parabolic run.
Again, I am not saying this will happen, but:

- I think this isn't like the top mania we've seen in previous cycles.
- It's good to consider this (brutal) scenario as a possibility.
- For me, the points of interest are the 0.25 reclaim or the range low retest for the potential continuation of the altcoin run. This could happen next week or in 6 months. I'll stay patient and react rather than predict.

In the meantime, we have the Euros to win.

To every person who’s represented the Pudgy Penguin as their PFP,  contributed to building around the IP, and to every member who’s helped create an ecosystem and culture that people are proud to be a part of, I just want to say thank you. 

The greatness of the Pudgy Penguin has been predestined since mint, and anybody with a knack for culture and community could see that. Yet, through every narrative possible, they tried to defeat us. Unfortunately for them, Penguins do not fold, and we do not falter. 

Our takeover was not a democratic process, but together, we turned our fate around. I believe a Web3 company is defined not by the technology it uses, but by the nature in which you build. I’ve been a strong advocate that to succeed, our team would have to be the muscle to the brain that is constructed around our NFT holders. It’s this hive-mind approach that has been the driving factor in our success and why I believe we are all responsible for where we are today. 

Today, the Pudgy Penguins brand is driven around a purpose that has been defined around solving 2 problems:

Problem 1: Web3 has a serious branding/top of the funnel problem.

Problem 2: Web3 has a extreme distribution problem.

Today, I can say confidently, that we are leading the charge in solving these 2 issues and our success in solving these problems has inspired other projects to do the same. You may not see it today, but as I look into the future, I see this snowball effect changing our industry forever. 

The Pudgy Penguins' success is not just our success, it’s everyone who believes in Web3s success. 

Though the belief around the Penguin has never been stronger, it is important to realize that we are far from where we want to be. We must remain steadfast as we continue our mission to onboard the masses. 

The story we’re telling here is the thesis of Web3 personified, and though we’ve helped shepard this story, we are not responsible for it. You are. 

I am excited to end this year with some more amazing moments and show the world in 2024 what Penguins can really do.

My whole life I went to private Jewish schools in Southern California. Growing up we had armed guards outside our double gates. Multiple former special ops military guys carrying AR’s outside and around entry points.

About once a year we had students from the local UC show up to protest… college adults protesting our existence at an elementary - high school. 
Semi-regularly had people call in threats. 
Multiple times over the years had to evacuate or couldn’t go to school for a day.

My friends from outside of school would so affectionately call me “my little jew bagel”. Joke that they liked my nose. Try to convert me to “save me from going to hell.” Tell me I’m lucky that I don’t look Jewish. Send me images of Palestinians and told it was “my fault” even though… I’m not Israeli… I’ve never even been to Israel…

When I would get upset they would tell me they were just joking, I obviously just needed to lighten up. 
They wouldn’t actually be doing it seriously? Who would do that, right? They were my friends…

So, after a while I did. 
I stopped fighting back. 
I stopped telling them it hurt me. 
It was one of me vs. all of them and if they told me it wasn’t a big deal, I guess it wasn’t a big deal… right?

I’ve realized over the last few weeks how common this experience is for most American Jews.
Going to school with armed guards in the middle of well established and “safe” parts of America.
Being demeaned but then invalidated if it upset us, learning to brush things off because it was easier than always trying to fight back. 
Being outnumbered constantly, told “well you’re my only Jewish friend but you’re one of the cool ones!”

Now being told, “you’re upset about antisemitism but HOW DO YOU THINK ____ FEEL ABOUT ___ (fill in the blank)”

I talked to a friend recently. His young son currently goes one of the same schools I went to — 14 years since I’ve graduated, it’s still the same. 
Armed guards. Double gated. Occasional threats and protests. 

14 years later… 27 years since I started school and not a single thing has changed.

Jewish children being protested against by grown adults. Being viciously “held accountable” for the actions of a government thousands of miles away where many of us haven’t even been. Constantly told our fear and sadness is invalid. Made to feel like it’s okay for other cultures to have and foster their community but when we do it we have an “underground society” where we “greedily control everything”.

Every single Jewish friend I have knows someone who was personally present, k^lled or captured on October 7th. 
Yet, they aren’t allowed to mourn. They haven’t been allowed to share grief. They have been busy fielding hate messages, comments, and antisemitism. 
Constantly screaming into the void for anyone to care like we all cared and advocated over the last few years for Black lives, Asian lives, gay lives and yes… for many of us even Palestinian lives.

Your Jewish friends are tired.
Not just because of the last few weeks, but because this is a culmination of a lifetime of fighting and worrying about our right to just simply exist. We have all been told, shown, subconsciously programmed into thinking “there are people who do not believe you should be alive regardless of what you do, regardless of where you stand, regardless of how much you contribute.”, and the last few weeks have just confirmed it.

That’s it.

Bugün 8 Eylül 2024. Kripto piyasası ne durumda, altcoinlere ne olacak, önümüzde bizi neler bekliyor ona bakacağız.

ÖZET: En baştan söylemek istiyorum, Kriptoda Pozitifim, yükseliş beklentim var. 

Uzun süren bir ayı piyasasını geride bırakıyoruz. Yükseliş (ralli) öncesi son bıktırma aşamalarında olduğumuzu düşünüyorum. Geçmişe gidersek; bu bölge tahminlerime göre daha uzun sürdü. Beklentim daha önce yukarı yönlü hareketti, takip edenler hatırlıyordur.

Elimizdeki tüm teknik ve psikolojik veriler ışında güzel bir “altsezon” un kaçınılmaz olduğunu düşünüyorum. Bu yazıda elimizdeki tüm verileri 2 ana başlıkta inceleyeceğiz. Ayrıca yaptığım gözlemlerde bahsedeceğim.

Temel stratejim; doğru bölgelerden uygun maliyetle imkânım kadar Altcoin toplamak, uzun vade düşünüp ona göre plan yapmak. Trendin sonuna doğru da parça parça satıp çıkmaktır. Günlük hesaplar yapmam, kaldıraçlı işlem almam, grafiklere haftalık ve aylık bakarım. Kısaca kriptoya göre uzun vadeli yatırım yaparım diyebilirim. 7 yılı geçen kripto deneyimime göre; en kolay ve en stressiz para kazanma şekli budur kriptoda. 

Boğa; saatlik günlük bir şey değildir. Trend bir süreçtir. Burada boğa sezonu olarak zamana yayılan bir olgudan bahsediyorum. Trend öyle 3-4 ayda bir değişmez. Yani her kısa harekette bir ayıya bir boğaya girilmez. Düzeltmeler bazen uzun sürebilir. 

Teknik Kısım

Grafikleri inceleyeceğiz. Genelde yazılı şekilde grafik anlatmam ama bu sefer anlatıyorum. Teknik verileri geçmiş döngülerle karşılaştırarak aşağı yukarı nerede olduğumuzu çizmeye çalışacağım. Döngüsel inceleme – “geçmişte böyle olmuş o zaman yine öyle olmalı” demek değildir. Bizim amacımız döngüsel benzerlikleri ve farkları mümkün olduğunca doğru yakalamaktır. Bu sayede yerimizi tespit edip önümüzü tahmin etmeye çalışırız. 
Bunun için genelde; kripto özelinde geçmiş veriye sahip majör altcoinleri incelerim. (Ethereum, Litecoin, Stellar Lumens (Xlm), Ripple (Xrp), Siacoin, Dash, Monero, Digibyte, Verge, Neo vs.)

#Solana TVL Surpasses $6.1 Billion

Total Value Locked (TVL) represents the overall value of assets that users have invested in a project.

According to DefiLlama, as of October 15, over 40 million #SOL is locked in decentralized protocols on Solana. At the start of 2024, this figure stood at 14 million SOL.

The decentralized exchange (DEX) Raydium has played a significant role in boosting Solana’s TVL to record highs.

Since the beginning of October, the total value locked on the network has surged by $1 billion, with Raydium alone accounting for $600 million of that increase.

CoinGecko data shows that the market cap of “meme” coins on Solana now exceeds $11 billion, with daily trading volumes nearing $4 billion.

According to IntoTheBlock, the number of daily active addresses on Solana has set a new record. On some days in October, the network recorded over 4 million active users, and since September, daily users have consistently surpassed 3 million.

1 NFT/1 wallet.

Contributions of #Web3D to the #RWA Ecosystem 

Web3 Decision aims to revolutionize the Real World Asset (RWA) ecosystem by integrating AI-powered tools and blockchain technology to create a more secure, transparent, and efficient framework for tokenizing and managing real-world assets.

Key Contributions:

  Enhanced Security with Logic-Based Smart Contracts
Web3 Decision employs logic-based smart contracts to eliminate the risks of human error and fraud in RWA transactions. These contracts ensure that all processes are automated, rule-driven, and tamper-proof, providing unparalleled security.

 Transparent Asset Tokenization
By leveraging blockchain technology, Web3 Decision offers a transparent and immutable record of asset ownership, transactions, and histories. This transparency increases trust among participants and reduces disputes.

 AI-Powered #riskmanagement Assessment
The project’s AI agents analyze historical data, market trends, and regulatory conditions to provide a comprehensive risk assessment for tokenized assets. This enables investors and asset owners to make informed decisions.

Dynamic Asset Valuation
Web3 Decision uses #AI algorithms to perform accurate and real-time asset valuations, ensuring fair pricing and enhancing the efficiency of RWA trading markets.

Regulatory Compliance
The platform provides tools to ensure compliance with regional and global regulations, simplifying the tokenization process for real-world assets and making it accessible to a broader audience.

Efficient Ownership Transfers
Web3 Decision streamlines the transfer of ownership for tokenized assets, reducing transaction times and costs. The use of blockchain ensures that these transfers are secure and immutable.

Scalability for Diverse Asset Types
The platform is designed to handle various asset classes, including real estate, commodities, and intellectual property, making it a versatile solution for RWA tokenization.

Community and Ecosystem Growth
By providing tools for tokenomics optimization and market analysis, Web3 Decision fosters growth within the RWA ecosystem, attracting more participants and increasing market liquidity.

Why It Matters:

Web3 Decision’s contributions will not only enhance the efficiency and security of the RWA ecosystem but also democratize access to investment opportunities, enabling a broader audience to participate in tokenized real-world assets.

Web3 Decision is set to become a cornerstone of the RWA revolution, bridging the gap between traditional assets and the decentralized economy.

"Believe in #Blockchain but always A Deep Review  #Crypto"

In the ever-evolving landscape of digital innovation, blockchain stands tall as a beacon of reliability and transparency. Its potential to revolutionize industries—finance, supply chain, healthcare, and beyond—is undeniable. Yet, as with any transformative technology, its application in cryptocurrency comes with challenges that demand scrutiny and critical thinking.

Blockchain: Trust Beyond Doubt

Blockchain is not just a buzzword; it's a robust, decentralized ledger system designed to provide secure and immutable records. Its architecture eliminates the need for centralized intermediaries, offering trust through transparency. This trust has fueled a wave of innovation, enabling smart contracts, decentralized applications (dApps), and tokenized ecosystems.

The beauty of blockchain lies in its simplicity: every transaction is recorded, verified, and stored in a distributed manner, making tampering nearly impossible. It's a system that demands belief—not blind faith, but a well-grounded confidence in its underlying principles.

Crypto: A Double-Edged Sword

Cryptocurrency, built on blockchain, has sparked a financial revolution. Bitcoin, Ethereum, and countless altcoins have introduced new forms of value exchange, investment, and community-driven economies. However, this innovation also opens doors to misuse (suistimal edilebilir).

From rug pulls to scams, the crypto space has witnessed its fair share of pitfalls. The decentralized nature of blockchain, while a strength, can also be exploited by bad actors. The lack of regulation and the rapid pace of development mean that investors and users must tread carefully.

Bridging the Gap: Belief with Caution

To "believe in blockchain" is to embrace its transformative power while remaining vigilant about its applications. Here are a few principles to guide this belief:

1. Education First: Understand the fundamentals of blockchain and crypto. Knowledge is the first step to protecting yourself and making informed decisions.

2. Due Diligence: Before investing or participating in any crypto project, research thoroughly. Look for transparency, utility, and a solid roadmap.

3. Advocating Ethics: As builders and contributors in the blockchain space, we must uphold ethical practices and design systems that prioritize security and user trust.

Conclusion

Blockchain is the future, but it needs responsible innovation to reach its full potential. Cryptocurrencies, as its most prominent application, should not overshadow the integrity of the technology itself.

By believing in blockchain while critically evaluating its use in crypto, we can strike a balance—embracing innovation without succumbing to the risks.

米国のベンチャーキャピタルである a16z（Andreessen Horowitz）が、テクノロジートレンドを予測して毎年発表しています

カテゴリがいくつかに分かれていますが、「BIG IDEAS 2025」のゲーム分野を抜粋します。
予測トレンドは大きく分けて4つです。
① 次世代のピクサー誕生の可能性
② 自分だけの内面世界を持つAIコンパニオン
③ ゲーム技術が未来のビジネスを支える
④ 顔出しなしクリエイターの第二波

概要は以下です
ーーーーーーーーーーーーーーー
① 次世代のピクサー誕生の可能性
  AIを活用した新技術「インタラクティブビデオ」により、映画とゲームを融合させた新しいエンターテインメントが生まれると期待されています。

【現在の課題】
・ゲームは従来、事前に作成した素材やエンジンに依存。
・開発に膨大な時間とコストがかかる。

【未来の姿】
・AIがプレイヤーの操作に応じて映像をリアルタイム生成。
・無限かつ個別化された体験を提供。
・テレビや映画の手軽さとゲームのインタラクティブ性を融合。

【期待される未来】
映画、ゲーム、AIを統合する新たなメディア企業が台頭し、次世代の「ピクサー」のような存在になる可能性がある。
ーーーーーーーーーーーーーーー
② 自分だけの内面世界を持つAIコンパニオン
AIコンパニオンが「内面世界」を持つことで、よりリアルで魅力的な存在になると期待されています。

【現在の課題】
・ユーザーの会話に反応するだけの受動的な存在。  
・独自の友人や背景を持たない。

【未来の姿】
・仮想の友人や感情を持ち、ニュースや出来事に反応。  
・自分の目的や欲求を持ちながら、ユーザーの人生にも共感。  
・ユーザーとの関係が双方向に進化。

【期待される未来】
AIが「自分の世界を生きている」と感じられることで、さらに親しみやすい存在になる。
ーーーーーーーーーーーーーーー
③ ゲーム技術が未来のビジネスを支える
ゲーム技術がエンターテインメントを超えて、さまざまな業界に浸透し、ビジネスの運営を変革しつつあります。

【現在の課題】
・仮想環境の構築やシミュレーションに多大なコストがかかる。
・現実と仮想をつなぐ技術の活用が限定的。

【未来の姿】
・生成AIが仮想コンテンツ作成のコストを大幅に削減。
・3Dキャプチャ技術により現実世界をデジタル化（デジタルツイン）。
・次世代XRデバイスが没入型体験を可能にし、業務効率を向上。

【具体的な事例】
・Anduril: 防衛シミュレーションでゲームエンジンを活用。
・Tesla: 自動運転システムの仮想訓練環境を構築。
・BMW: ARを活用した次世代ヘッドアップディスプレイを開発。
・Matterport: バーチャル内覧で不動産業界を変革。
・Traverse3D: 労働者向けの仮想トレーニングを支援。

【期待される未来】
2025年には、ゲーム技術が訓練、買い物、労働力育成などあらゆる分野に浸透し、産業全体を変革すると予測されている。
ーーーーーーーーーーーーーーー
④ 顔出しなしクリエイターの第二波
外見を隠しながら動画を作成する「顔出しなしクリエイター」が、AI技術を活用し、新たな可能性を広げています。

【現在の課題】
・コンテンツ制作には依然としてカメラや高価な機材が必要とされる場合が多い。
・言語や声の壁が一部のクリエイターにとって障害となる。

【未来の姿】
・AIソフトウェアにより、カメラや機材が不要で手軽に高品質な動画が制作可能。
・非母国語や異なる声での表現も実現。
・例：インドのクリエイターがフランス語訛りで動画エッセイを制作するなど、表現の幅が広がる。

【具体的な事例】
・声のみで活動するクリエイター。
・仮装やキャラクターを使って顔を隠すクリエイター。
・VTuberのように仮想アバターで活動するクリエイター。

【期待される未来】
視聴者は顔ではなく、情報の有益性や娯楽性を重視するようになり、顔出しにとらわれない多様なクリエイターが活躍する時代が訪れると期待されている。

FujinさんのWeb3ゲームコミュニティ『Zephyrs(
@Zephyrs_Guild
)』で開催される「Game Night」2回目のゲームは『Legendary Heroes Unchained(
@LHUGame
) 』。

このWeb3ゲームはソシャゲで馴染みが深い「ターン制コマンドバトルRPG」だったため、PSの無い自分のようなソシャゲ中心のプレイヤーでも楽しむことができます。

まず最初に惹かれたのがキャラデザの良さ。
洋画風デザインなので日本人受けはあまり良くないかも知れませんが、個人的にはかなり好みでした
人系・獣人系・機械系・悪魔系など多種多様なデザインで、無料で誰でも貰える最低ランク「STARTER」でも、低レアにはとても見えないカッコ良さでしかも1体1体しっかりアニメーションまでがつけられているのがとても良いと感じました！
(しかも最大LVまで育成すれば、マーケットでNFTキャラクターとして売買可能とのこと！)

ホワイトペーパーも一通り読みましたが、ゲームナイトでFujinさんが言っていたように「ギルドを重要視している」という点など、今後長期的な視点でゲームを発展させていく明確な方向性が見え、実現可能性も高そうに感じました。
https://legendaryheroesunchained.com/vision

[ロードマップのイメージ]
(1)エポック1: 英雄の時代(NFTヒーローメイン)
↓
(2)エポック2: ギルドの時代 (ランドNFTやトークンなどギルドメイン)
↓
(3)エポック3: 戦争の時代(ギルド間の戦闘やエコシステム)
↓
(4)エポック4: 創造の時代(オープンソース化、独自のゲーム、DAOなど)

今まで見てきたゲームだとまだゲームのリリースもされていないのに、いきなり「高額LAND NFT」を販売というパターンも多かったので、まずゲームリリース、そしてその後ギルドコンテンツの発展という『Legendary Heroes Unchained』のロードマップは、とても新鮮でこのゲームが将来どうなっていくのか是非観てみたい！と感じました。
